1
00:01:19,340 --> 00:01:27,340
(THE SPIREALM)

2
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:31,990
(Episode 15)

3
00:01:32,870 --> 00:01:34,930
What do you have to talk with me about?

4
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:36,550
Didn't you claim to remember

5
00:01:36,550 --> 00:01:38,289
whatever happened in the school?

6
00:01:38,289 --> 00:01:40,110
We'd like to ask you about someone.

7
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:40,750
Who?

8
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:41,750
Sachiko.

9
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:47,430
I-I don't know about her.

10
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:51,039
Two years ago, outside the school,

11
00:01:51,270 --> 00:01:52,870
a student had a car accident.

12
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,229
You know that, right?

13
00:01:58,229 --> 00:02:00,110
It's been a long time.

14
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:02,740
Why are you bringing it up now?

15
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,820
You do know about this student,

16
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:05,820
don't you?

17
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:12,110
She was bullied by all of her classmates at school.

18
00:02:13,110 --> 00:02:15,870
After she died, a number of students composed

19
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,870
a song based on her death to mock her.

20
00:02:17,950 --> 00:02:19,430
Did she deserve all that suffering

21
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:21,490
simply because she had a poor family?

22
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:36,670
That girl was named Sachiko.

23
00:02:38,870 --> 00:02:40,130
Not only did I know her,

24
00:02:40,829 --> 00:02:42,910
I also knew her grandparents.

25
00:02:45,350 --> 00:02:46,510
Her grandparents?

26
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:48,590
What about her parents?

27
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:51,110
They died.

28
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:57,070
A car accident happened on their way to deliver fish,

29
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:00,190
and killed them both.

30
00:03:01,230 --> 00:03:02,790
Her parents had a car accident,

31
00:03:02,790 --> 00:03:03,950
and so did she.

32
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:05,390
Poor thing.

33
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,910
Later on,

34
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:09,590
a reporter found out about this,

35
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,950
and thought it could make a good news.

36
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:17,070
So he went to her home and did an interview.

37
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:18,720
He took some photos too.

38
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:22,550
Do you have the news report and the photos?

39
00:03:22,550 --> 00:03:23,680
Let me find them out.

40
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,470
Look.

41
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,950
(Victim of the accident, Sachiko)

42
00:03:44,950 --> 00:03:46,790
She's a pretty little girl.

43
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:49,200
Why was she repelled by others?

44
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:52,230
Could it be that her classmates felt jealous of her?

45
00:03:52,230 --> 00:03:53,310
Anyway,

46
00:03:53,950 --> 00:03:55,350
she was isolated.

47
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:57,510
Look what the reporter wrote here.

48
00:03:57,510 --> 00:03:58,590
So much gossip.

49
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,070
The whole piece is about

50
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:02,950
Sachiko's embarrassing stories at school.

51
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:05,270
The reporters in those times

52
00:04:05,470 --> 00:04:07,270
would do anything to make money.

53
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:11,630
These photos reflect the road conditions when the accident happened.

54
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:14,920
It happened on a road in a remote place.

55
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:16,510
There shouldn't be too many cars.

56
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:18,839
Drivers would have a good view of the road.

57
00:04:19,029 --> 00:04:20,630
Why didn't people further investigate

58
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:22,089
the cause of the accident?

59
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:24,240
Because it was hard, unimportant,

60
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,110
or just unworthy.

61
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,190
Sachiko's bedroom.

62
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:33,940
Judging from this photo,

63
00:04:34,630 --> 00:04:36,230
her family was really poor.

64
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:38,800
But why would such a poor family

65
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,120
let their daughter

66
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,450
go to such a nice school?

67
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:46,159
Because they wanted to reshape their lives with knowledge.

68
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:49,230
Hold on.

69
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:52,740
(Sachiko's bedroom)

70
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:54,740
The bamboo basket in this photo

71
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:56,870
is identical to the one I saw yesterday.

72
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:58,270
I remember you telling me

73
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,410
that you first saw this basket

74
00:05:00,990 --> 00:05:02,250
in the School Archive.

75
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:06,470
I didn't know it belonged to Sako.

76
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:11,870
Thank you.

77
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:14,110
No problem.

78
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:17,710
To be honest, you are the first people

79
00:05:17,910 --> 00:05:21,270
to show so much care for Sachiko.

80
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:25,670
I hope you'll restore justice

81
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:27,870
for Sachiko.

82
00:05:28,550 --> 00:05:30,590
Rest assured. We will.

83
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,390
Let's go.

84
00:05:39,670 --> 00:05:40,670
It's still here.

85
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:48,110
It's adorable.

86
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:50,150
In my childhood, when I was upset,

87
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:52,480
I would also draw smiling faces on my toys,

88
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,110
just to cheer myself up.

89
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,110
Did you hear that?

90
00:06:02,590 --> 00:06:04,030
Hear what?

91
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,740
Why are you always startled?

92
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:08,030
I heard a girl's laughter.

93
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:10,850
Where did it come from?

94
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:16,030
Now it's gone.

95
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:22,270
This basket must belong to Sachiko.

96
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:24,110
Her ghost goes everywhere with it.

97
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:25,840
The one you saw in the dormitory

98
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:26,950
must be hers too.

99
00:06:29,110 --> 00:06:30,110
Let's go.

100
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:01,750
It looks like the key to the exit

101
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,310
is connected to Sachiko.

102
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:06,950
Now we've only figured out her ghost's motive to kill,

103
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:09,210
but we still don't know how to get the key.

104
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:12,470
Is destroying Sachiko's ghost the only way

105
00:07:12,550 --> 00:07:13,950
to find the key?

106
00:07:14,310 --> 00:07:15,440
Why would we do that?

107
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,880
Sachiko was the one being bullied.

108
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,710
What's up? Are you in a bad mood?

109
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,440
I just feel sorry for her.

110
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,220
What she was put through

111
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:26,630
might be more terrible than we think.

112
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,790
What on earth did you say?

113
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:29,110
I didn't say anything.

114
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:30,910
Is that Jiang Xinhong?

115
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:33,150
Why wouldn't you believe me?

116
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:35,510
I'm just a little scared.

117
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,870
Fear can't help you with anything now.

118
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:39,110
Just get through this period of time,

119
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:40,909
and you'll be fine once you start college.

120
00:07:40,909 --> 00:07:43,240
Why are you so sure I'll be fine in college?

121
00:07:43,909 --> 00:07:45,909
What if her ghost follows me to college?

122
00:07:45,909 --> 00:07:46,990
You can go find her.

123
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:49,310
Let's see if she'll spare your life.

124
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,310
It's all your fault.

125
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:53,250
Don't you talk nonsense anymore!

126
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,190
Watch your mouth.

127
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,640
What are you doing here?

128
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:10,310
Spill it. What else do you know?

129
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:12,310
I've told you everything I know.

130
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:16,170
Did that classmate of yours ask you to keep a secret?

131
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,710
That's a private matter between him and me.

132
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:24,840
Let me venture a guess here.

133
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,960
You and he are related to Sachiko's death.

134
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:30,510
Sachiko's ghost kills in the school

135
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:31,750
with the purpose of finding you and him.

136
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,830
It's not like that.

137
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,740
Then what's the truth?

138
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:42,250
If you don't tell us what you know,

139
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:44,960
how are we supposed to help you?

140
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,440
Okay.

141
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:53,270
Sachiko was transferred to our class

142
00:08:53,270 --> 00:08:54,750
in 10th grade.

143
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:57,790
All the classmates at that time

144
00:08:58,420 --> 00:09:00,020
were from wealthy families.

145
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:01,950
No one expected

146
00:09:01,950 --> 00:09:04,950
that a child of fish sellers could afford school.

147
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:07,070
Plus, in our class,

148
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:09,600
Sachiko performed quite well academically.

149
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,970
Out of jealousy, many other students

150
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:14,350
gave her the cold shoulder.

151
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:19,110
Have you smelled it?

152
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:20,970
There's a gross fish smell on her!

153
00:09:21,190 --> 00:09:22,950
Maybe it's because she has to sell fish

154
00:09:22,950 --> 00:09:25,190
on her way home after school!

155
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:40,270
Thank you.

156
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:41,350
Jiang Xinhong!

157
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:43,780
Why did you have to let her pick up the ball?

158
00:09:43,780 --> 00:09:45,120
Now the ball has a gross fish smell.

159
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,710
How are we supposed to play with it?

160
00:09:46,710 --> 00:09:47,990
Go and wash it now!

161
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:50,110
I don't wanna be stunk up by that smell!

162
00:09:50,110 --> 00:09:51,110
Hurry up!

163
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:53,630
What were you thinking?

164
00:09:53,990 --> 00:09:55,000
So stinky!

165
00:09:55,670 --> 00:09:58,030
Everyone took pleasure in bullying her.

166
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,730
Sachiko wasn't angry about it.

167
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:03,840
So people started to escalate their acts.

168
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,430
There hasn't been much fun in recent days.

169
00:10:09,430 --> 00:10:10,070
Yeah.

170
00:10:10,070 --> 00:10:11,550
Aren't we going on a spring outing in two days?

171
00:10:11,550 --> 00:10:13,080
Spring outings are boring.

172
00:10:13,190 --> 00:10:14,270
We're tired of going to the park.

173
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:15,270
A spring outing?

174
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,110
I have an idea!

175
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:19,360
In the upcoming spring outing,

176
00:10:19,830 --> 00:10:22,060
why don't we play a prank on that fish selling girl?

177
00:10:22,060 --> 00:10:22,830
Sure!

178
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:23,830
No.

179
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:26,330
What kind of prank should we pull?

180
00:10:26,950 --> 00:10:28,680
Let's huddle up and discuss it.

181
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,870
I knew that was wrong.

182
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:34,030
But I was afraid that if I helped her,

183
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:35,750
I would be isolated by the others.

184
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:38,550
That's why I never had the guts to tell her about it.

185
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:40,600
Then on the day of the spring outing...

186
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,710
Everyone, gather around!

187
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:44,470
Let's take a group photo, okay?

188
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:45,190
Okay!

189
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:46,190
Come on. Come here.

190
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:47,250
Let's take a photo.

191
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,360
Hurry!

192
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:54,950
Grab a seat and sit down.

193
00:10:58,710 --> 00:10:59,910
Don't come over here!

194
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,610
I don't want to sit next to you.

195
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,030
There's a bad smell on you.

196
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:04,030
It stinks.

197
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:07,390
Is she gonna join us? Then I don't wanna be in this photo.

198
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,390
Nor do I.

199
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,770
We don't wanna be in the photo either.

200
00:11:12,030 --> 00:11:13,430
Mr. Liu, do something!

201
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:16,550
How are we supposed to take a group photo with her around?

202
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,310
Her stink is making me woozy!

203
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:19,750
Go away!

204
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:20,900
Hurry up!

205
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:27,490
Guys, come back here for the group photo.

206
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,110
Come back now!

207
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,710
Let's have fun after taking this photo!

208
00:11:30,710 --> 00:11:31,710
Okay.

209
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:33,630
Look at me!

210
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:36,710
Three, two, one.

211
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:41,790
Okay.

212
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:43,190
Everyone's free to move.

213
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:44,310
Be careful

214
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,350
of danger.

215
00:11:45,510 --> 00:11:46,870
Okay.

216
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:49,950
Did she go that way?

217
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:51,350
Let's go.

218
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:04,470
Sachiko, let's play a game, alright?

219
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:09,800
Don't leave in such a hurry.

220
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:11,230
Look what this is.

221
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:14,310
Why are you holding my diary?

222
00:12:14,470 --> 00:12:15,190
Give it to me!

223
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:16,270
Stop trying to grab it.

224
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:17,510
Give it to me!

225
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:18,870
- Stand still! - Let go of me!

226
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:20,070
That's mine!

227
00:12:20,190 --> 00:12:21,670
Let me read it to you. What do you think?

228
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:22,710
Sounds fine to me!

229
00:12:23,150 --> 00:12:25,350
On February 3, it was a sunny day.

230
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:28,140
Although it was already a late winter,

231
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,350
it was still a little cold.

232
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:32,950
It was still a little cold.

233
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,070
I was on my way to...

234
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:36,390
To deliver the fish.

235
00:12:38,190 --> 00:12:40,470
I felt like my hand was cracked.

236
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,750
Cracked.

237
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:45,750
Why do I have to live like this?

238
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:47,390
It's well written.

239
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,390
Let go of me!

240
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:49,950
Give it back to me!

241
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:51,710
Get lost!

242
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,150
You deserve it.

243
00:12:57,670 --> 00:13:00,270
You're just a fish seller, but you acted all hoity-toity.

244
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:02,330
I'll make you show who you really are.

245
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:05,080
Do it.

246
00:13:06,710 --> 00:13:08,080
Let me give you a shower!

247
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:14,000
It's pleasant to see you like this now.

248
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,870
Sachiko, I'm warning you.

249
00:13:17,470 --> 00:13:20,510
Acting all hoity-toity, huh? Who do you think you are?

250
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:22,820
Let's go.

251
00:13:23,710 --> 00:13:24,710
The next day,

252
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:28,950
everyone knew that Sachiko died in a car accident.

253
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:32,310
But no one cared.

254
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:35,570
It was as if a totally unrelated person had died.

255
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,870
They even made up a song to laugh at her.

256
00:13:40,310 --> 00:13:41,550
Since that day,

257
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:44,470
some of her classmates died mysteriously.

258
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,990
Everyone was so scared.

259
00:13:47,950 --> 00:13:49,310
My class was separated

260
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:51,850
and divided into different classes.

261
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:54,790
But death kept happening.

262
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,470
Did Sachiko ever come to you?

263
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,230
You all laughed at her,

264
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:05,390
but why did you survive?

265
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:09,790
Maybe I'm the only one in the class

266
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:11,630
who didn't read her diary.

267
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:15,230
I've never sung the song

268
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,030
made up to laugh at her.

269
00:14:19,390 --> 00:14:21,990
He hasn't triggered the taboo conditions yet.

270
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:26,710
This group photo was taken that day?

271
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:32,270
I've said everything.

272
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,140
Can I leave now?

273
00:14:34,590 --> 00:14:36,390
Who is he that just talked to you?

274
00:14:36,990 --> 00:14:38,190
Is he your classmate?

275
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:41,730
His name is Mou Kai.

276
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,270
He has transferred to another school

277
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:44,400
and is going abroad.

278
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:46,830
Can I go now?

279
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:48,390
Yes.

280
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:49,910
If there's anything else,

281
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:51,110
we'll find you again.

282
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:58,550
A teenager girl

283
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:01,510
